Explain the difference between execute(), executeQuery() and executeUpdate() methods in JDBC.
Answer:-

execute():--
This method can be used any type of SQL statements like DDL,DML,DRL,DCL.
this method return boolean type of value.

executeQuery():--
This method can be used only for DRL operations.
it executes only select statements.
it returns resultset object.

executeUpdate():--
This method can be use only for DML operations.
it is used for update,delete,insert operations.
this method return int type of value.
